threepio.engine
Class Threepio

java.lang.Object
  threepio.engine.Threepio

public class Threepio
extends java.lang.Object

The Threepio class is the high-level processor for XML/BBF Data Model processing and diffing. It should be controlled by a separate UI, like ThreepioFrame.

Author:
jhoule
See Also:
TRminatorGUI

                                        java.lang.String pathIn,
                                        java.io.File fileOut,
                                        java.lang.String majorItemType,
                                        boolean diff,
                                        boolean profiles,
                                        boolean looks)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
docToPrintedTable turns an XDoc object into a ModelTable object, and prints it out as an HTML table, to a file.

Parameters:
cols - - an IHM of the columns to use for the table.
ID - - the ID of the body in the file to put into the ModelTable.
pathIn - - the path for the file to examine.
fileOut - - the file to place the ModelTable into.
majorItemType - - the type of item that defines a row
diff - - denotes whether or not to diff the model against the model before it.
profiles - - denotes whether or not to append a table of Model items from doc(s)
looks - - denotes whether or not to add newlines (HTML) to make the info fit in a table.
Returns:
true if the table was produced correctly, false if there was a problem.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - - in the case of any error returned by subroutines.
